         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.709-6</ph> Contract clause.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d2530e8" class="- topic/p ">Use the clause at <xref href="52.242-3.dita#FAR_52_242_3"
                  base="FAR_52_242_3"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.242-3</xref>, Penalties for
Unallowable Costs, in all solicitations and contracts over <ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 2, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$800,000<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 42.709-6 by removing “$750,000” and adding “$800,000” in its place.?></ph> except fixed-price
contracts without cost incentives or any firm-fixed-price contract
for the purchase of commercial items. Generally, covered contracts
are those which contain one of the clauses at <xref href="52.216-7.dita#FAR_52_216_7"
                  base="FAR_52_216_7"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-7</xref>, <xref href="52.216-16.dita#FAR_52_216_16"
                  base="FAR_52_216_16"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-16</xref>, or <xref href="52.216-17.dita#FAR_52_216_17"
                  base="FAR_52_216_17"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">52.216-17</xref>, or a similar
clause from an executive agency’s supplement to the FAR.</p>
